So far, the food pantry has made 1,758 disbursements this year.

337 of these disbursements have gone to the Graduate School of Engineering and Applied Science. The school has received 19 percent of disbursements and makes up 11 percent of the total student body population. This is followed by the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences (8 percent of the student body population) with 284 disbursements and Teachers College (13 percent of the student body population) with 278.
